Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
HOUSE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. ____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION recognizing Heisman
2 Trophy winner Fernando Mendoza.
3 Whereas, Indiana University quarterback Fernando Mendoza
4 was awarded the 91st Heisman Trophy on December 13, 2025,
5 becoming Indiana University's first player to win the
6 prestigious award;
7 Whereas, Fernando Mendoza was an easy pick for the trophy,
8 finishing first in all six voting regions after leading the
9 Hoosiers to a 2025 Big Ten Championship win over Ohio State
10 University;
11 Whereas, Fernando Mendoza completed 273 of 379 passes,
12 a 72 percent pass completion rate, for 3,535 yards, 41
13 touchdowns, and six interceptions while rushing for 276 yards
14 and seven touchdowns on the season;
15 Whereas, After leading Indiana University to a College
16 Football Playoff National Championship win, Fernando
17 Mendoza became one of only 18 players in college football
18 history to win both the Heisman Trophy and the national
19 championship in the same season;
20 Whereas, Due to his success on the field, Fernando Mendoza
21 is projected to be the first overall pick in the 2026 NFL Draft;
22 Whereas, Fernando Mendoza earned the Heisman Trophy
23 through his dedication and determination as the best in the
24 sport, while never failing to credit his teammates for their
25 essential role in his success; and
2026 HC 1012/DI 140

2
1 Whereas, Fernando Mendoza is a stellar role model,
2 demonstrating strong faith, a love of family, and high moral
3 character: Therefore,
4 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives
5 of the General Assembly of the State of Indiana,
6 the Senate concurring:
7 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly recognizes
8 Heisman Trophy winner Fernando Mendoza of the Indiana
9 University Hoosiers football team.
10 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
11 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to
12 Indiana University Vice President and Director of
13 Intercollegiate Athletics Scott Dolson for distribution.
2026 HC 1012/DI 140

